In this proclamation, President Donald Trump declares June 2018 as Great Outdoors Month in the United States. He highlights the beauty of the nation's natural wonders such as mountains, waters, canyons, and coastlines, and encourages Americans to spend time outdoors, especially during the summer. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of access to public lands and the enjoyment of outdoor activities like fishing, camping, and hiking. President Trump also emphasizes the need to practice good stewardship of the environment and preserve natural lands and waters for future generations.